WEBVTT

00:01.837 --> 00:02.881
‐ You're not gonna hurt me.

00:02.881 --> 00:04.635
You're gonna let me go
right now,

00:04.635 --> 00:07.431
<i>or I'm gonna tell Nadia</i>
<i>the truth about you.</i>

00:07.431 --> 00:09.185
We both know
you can't have that.

00:09.185 --> 00:11.524
POP: Seeing you
in that white coat?

00:11.524 --> 00:14.780
I could check out tomorrow
knowing I done one good thing.

00:14.780 --> 00:16.784
<i>Let's save some time</i>
<i>and cut through the bullshit.</i>

00:16.784 --> 00:18.495
‐ I don't know
what you're insinuating‐‐

00:18.495 --> 00:19.957
POP: I'm not insinuating.
I'm telling.

00:19.957 --> 00:21.292
My nephew's missing.

00:21.292 --> 00:22.796
<i>ANNIE: I killed a man,</i>

00:22.796 --> 00:25.133
and then I took him to the pit
and I threw him in the hole.

00:25.133 --> 00:27.471
<i>That's not even</i>
<i>the worst of it.</i>

00:27.471 --> 00:29.225
He came back.

00:29.225 --> 00:30.645
<i>ACE: John Merrill.</i>

00:30.645 --> 00:33.483
‐ John as in, uh, Ace Merrill?

00:33.483 --> 00:35.530
<i>ANNIE: He's coming for us now.</i>

00:35.530 --> 00:38.703
<i>He's a very bad man.</i>

00:38.703 --> 00:40.372
<i>And he's not gonna stop.</i>

00:40.372 --> 00:43.253
POP: Thought you were dead,
you fucking moron!

00:43.253 --> 00:45.675
The fuck out of here!

00:45.675 --> 00:47.136
<i>JOY: The plan is,</i>
<i>I don't let you out</i>

00:47.136 --> 00:48.346
<i>until you take your pills.</i>

00:48.346 --> 00:50.392
ANNIE: Mom! Mom!
[blade slices]

00:50.392 --> 00:52.354
‐ [breathing heavily]
‐ Joy, Joy, Joy, Joy!

00:52.354 --> 00:53.398
Joy!

00:53.398 --> 00:55.903
[thunder rumbling]

01:01.414 --> 01:04.717
[waves crashing]

01:04.717 --> 01:06.723
[indistinct chatter]

01:11.414 --> 01:13.511
[Abdi and Nadia
speaking Somali]

01:32.811 --> 01:36.192
[wheels rattling]

01:41.369 --> 01:44.375
[helicopter rotors whirring]

01:48.216 --> 01:50.930
[whirring fades]

02:01.743 --> 02:04.373
[distant gunfire]

02:04.373 --> 02:05.960
[rocket whistles]

02:05.960 --> 02:08.465
[explosion]

02:33.123 --> 02:34.144
[gasps]

02:43.577 --> 02:46.583
[phone ringing]
[distant shouting]

02:46.583 --> 02:48.743
[helicopter rotors whirring]
[Abdi and Kalifo speaking Somalian]

02:50.883 --> 02:53.221
[distant shouting]

02:57.689 --> 02:58.941
Nadia!

03:05.871 --> 03:06.877
Nadia!

03:14.179 --> 03:15.223
‐ Right there.

03:17.436 --> 03:18.647
‐ Slow.

03:20.651 --> 03:22.947
SOLDIER:
[whispering] No house.

03:22.947 --> 03:25.201
No house.

03:25.201 --> 03:28.667
<i>[tense music]</i>
[Nadia speaking Somalian]

03:31.090 --> 03:31.770
KALIFO:
Abdi! Nadia!

03:36.254 --> 03:37.269
SOLDIER 1: She's got a weapon!
SOLDIER 2: Tell her to stop.

03:37.269 --> 03:37.852
‐ Nadia!

03:38.866 --> 03:40.023
SOLDIER: Drop the weapon! Drop it!
‐ [screams] Nadia!

03:40.023 --> 03:42.152
[gunshots]
[grunts]

03:45.033 --> 03:46.410
SOLDIER 1: Stay down.
SOLDIER 2: She's down!

03:53.346 --> 03:54.883
SOLDIER: Keep open.
There could be more.

04:09.289 --> 04:12.254
<i>[ominous music]</i>

04:12.254 --> 04:19.268
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:43.901 --> 04:46.907
<i>[tense music]</i>

04:46.907 --> 04:52.585
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:52.585 --> 04:55.591
[engine rumbling]

05:11.623 --> 05:14.128
‐ [breathing shakily]

05:14.128 --> 05:16.382
[brakes squeal]

05:21.058 --> 05:28.072
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:40.973 --> 05:43.102
[brakes squeal]

05:43.102 --> 05:45.733
‐ Evening, neighbor.

05:45.733 --> 05:46.735
Need a lift?

05:49.824 --> 05:51.202
How's your mother?

05:51.202 --> 05:53.039
‐ She's‐‐she's fine.

05:53.039 --> 05:55.001
ACE: Glad to hear it.

05:55.001 --> 05:56.963
Let me give you a ride.

05:56.963 --> 05:59.594
‐ Uh, th‐that‐‐that's my bus.

06:04.019 --> 06:05.313
[air hisses]

06:22.932 --> 06:24.602
JAMAL: Ready?

06:24.602 --> 06:26.105
NADIA: What?
‐ Saturday.

06:27.817 --> 06:30.154
‐ I can't, J.

06:30.154 --> 06:32.994
With this whole Pop situation,
it's a lot.

06:32.994 --> 06:34.454
‐ Come on,
you canceled last week.

06:34.454 --> 06:36.501
‐ [sighs]

06:37.670 --> 06:40.049
Apologies
for being late, Pastor.

06:40.049 --> 06:41.678
Long night.

06:41.678 --> 06:43.724
DREW: Anything I can do?

06:43.724 --> 06:45.310
NADIA: Does the Bible
say anything

06:45.310 --> 06:48.357
about how to stop a family
from killing each other?

06:48.357 --> 06:51.238
DREW: Yes, actually.

06:51.238 --> 06:54.077
NADIA: Anyway, sorry,
in a bit of a rush today.

06:54.077 --> 06:57.960
DREW: One fellow who needs
a pneumonia check and...

06:57.960 --> 07:00.339
her.

07:02.970 --> 07:09.984
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:09.984 --> 07:13.449
[insects buzzing]

07:13.449 --> 07:16.330
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:16.330 --> 07:18.084
[door thuds]

07:18.084 --> 07:21.090
[lock clicks, door creaks]

07:21.090 --> 07:26.768
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:26.768 --> 07:28.312
[drawer clatters]

07:29.690 --> 07:32.780
[metallic clanging]

07:32.780 --> 07:33.990
[door slams]
‐ [gasps]

07:33.990 --> 07:35.326
ANNIE: Joy?

07:35.326 --> 07:36.955
[metallic rattling]
[zipper whirrs]

07:38.499 --> 07:41.004
The mother's own fudge
are you doing?

07:41.004 --> 07:42.423
‐ Joy told me to get her shit.

07:42.423 --> 07:44.679
ANNIE: Where is she?

07:44.679 --> 07:47.977
‐ I don't know.
‐ Little liar.

07:47.977 --> 07:50.356
JOY: This is all my fault.

07:50.356 --> 07:53.445
I should have made sure that
she was swallowing the pills.

07:55.158 --> 07:58.372
‐ You didn't cause
any of this, Joy.

07:58.372 --> 08:00.627
JOY: [sighs]

08:00.627 --> 08:05.052
‐ Sometimes it helps
to feel like it's your fault...

08:05.052 --> 08:07.390
because that means
you've got control.

08:09.352 --> 08:11.858
You think, "If I broke it,

08:11.858 --> 08:14.196
then I can fix it."

08:14.196 --> 08:16.241
[helicopter rotors
whirring faintly]

08:16.241 --> 08:19.247
<i>[soft tense music]</i>

08:19.247 --> 08:21.586
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:21.586 --> 08:23.214
‐ I can.

08:23.214 --> 08:25.719
I could just go back

08:25.719 --> 08:29.560
and‐‐and‐‐and be good
like‐‐like before.

08:29.560 --> 08:31.188
‐ I need to talk to her!

08:31.188 --> 08:32.524
CHANCE: Should have
given her a phone, then.

08:32.524 --> 08:35.112
‐ You tell her that
she needs to come home now!

08:35.112 --> 08:39.120
‐ You almost killed your own
fucking daughter last night!

08:39.120 --> 08:40.414
‐ No.

08:40.414 --> 08:41.709
CHANCE: Look around you, lady.

08:42.628 --> 08:44.507
Look at your fucking face.

08:44.507 --> 08:47.011
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:47.011 --> 08:50.686
[door clicks open, slams]

08:50.686 --> 08:52.355
<i>JOY: Can I stay with you?</i>

08:52.355 --> 08:55.444
Just until
we figure everything out.

08:55.444 --> 08:56.948
‐ [sighs]

08:56.948 --> 08:58.785
JOY: Please?

08:58.785 --> 09:03.127
NADIA: Joy, we either have to
call the police or your mother.

09:03.127 --> 09:07.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:07.928 --> 09:10.851
[phone rings]

09:10.851 --> 09:13.147
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:13.147 --> 09:15.777
[indistinct chatter]

09:22.206 --> 09:25.463
ANNIE: Where is she?
‐ She's at my house.

09:25.463 --> 09:26.924
Look, it's better
than a shelter.

09:26.924 --> 09:28.469
She's safe.
She just wasn't ready to‐‐

09:28.469 --> 09:31.684
‐ Better with me than anywhere.
‐ She was covered in blood.

09:31.684 --> 09:33.688
‐ 'Cause the sutures opened up.

09:33.688 --> 09:35.692
[no audible dialogue]

09:35.692 --> 09:37.863
NADIA: Sit down, Anne.

09:41.119 --> 09:44.376
ANNIE: Look, I don't know
what yarn she's been spinning,

09:44.376 --> 09:47.966
but Joy's always had
quite an imagination.

09:47.966 --> 09:50.681
‐ She told me you're running...
from her father.

09:50.681 --> 09:53.435
Do you have full custody?

09:53.435 --> 09:56.818
‐ I don't know why I would
have to explain to you‐‐

09:56.818 --> 09:59.406
to a woman...

09:59.406 --> 10:02.955
why we had to run
from a violent man.

10:02.955 --> 10:04.416
‐ If you and Joy
are in danger‐‐

10:04.416 --> 10:06.879
‐ We weren't
until you decided to help.

10:06.879 --> 10:08.424
‐ She needs a stable home,

10:08.424 --> 10:10.010
and you need a specialist
supervising your care.

10:10.010 --> 10:11.388
‐ Christmas.

10:11.388 --> 10:12.516
‐ And I can't let you back
at the hospital.

10:12.516 --> 10:14.269
I'm sorry, Anne.

10:16.398 --> 10:18.903
Anne?

10:18.903 --> 10:25.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:29.675 --> 10:31.178
[knocking]

10:31.178 --> 10:33.432
‐ Joy!

10:33.432 --> 10:36.021
Come out here immediately!

10:36.021 --> 10:37.148
[gun cocking]

10:37.148 --> 10:38.985
‐ Get the fuck out of here.

10:38.985 --> 10:41.908
‐ I am here for my daughter.

10:41.908 --> 10:44.287
‐ She says she's not going.

10:44.287 --> 10:45.832
Her words.
‐ Please‐‐

10:45.832 --> 10:49.005
ABDI: Woman, she told us
what you did!

10:49.005 --> 10:50.592
Do not come back here.

10:50.592 --> 10:57.606
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:00.277 --> 11:03.242
‐ Joy!

11:03.242 --> 11:05.914
Joy!

11:05.914 --> 11:07.584
Joy!

11:10.841 --> 11:13.847
[beetles buzzing]

11:14.890 --> 11:16.393
[cassette case clicks]

11:20.025 --> 11:22.823
[tape whirring]

11:22.823 --> 11:24.117
<i>POP: All right,</i>
<i>let's just fucking play.</i>

11:24.117 --> 11:25.244
<i>All right.</i>

11:25.244 --> 11:27.331
<i>ABDI:</i>
<i>He can't hurt me, Pop.</i>

11:27.331 --> 11:31.172
[tape rewinding]

11:31.172 --> 11:33.343
<i>CHRIS:</i>
<i>Little homemade video here.</i>

11:33.343 --> 11:36.767
<i>POP: Oh, so cute, so cute.</i>
<i>Look at you guys.</i>

11:36.767 --> 11:38.605
<i>They don't play baseball</i>
<i>in Somalia, do they?</i>

11:38.605 --> 11:40.065
<i>ABDI:</i>
<i>Throw it to me!</i>

11:41.151 --> 11:42.403
<i>ACE: Okay.</i>

11:42.403 --> 11:43.573
Okay.

11:43.573 --> 11:44.783
<i>What's your problem?</i>

11:44.783 --> 11:46.411
<i>CHRIS:</i>
<i>Everyone puts a card down,</i>

11:46.411 --> 11:47.623
<i>and whoever has</i>
<i>the highest card</i>

11:47.623 --> 11:49.125
<i>takes all the cards</i>
<i>that are there.</i>

11:49.125 --> 11:50.670
<i>And whoever with the most</i>
<i>cards at the end wins.</i>

11:50.670 --> 11:52.256
[door clicks open]
<i>You got it?</i>

11:52.256 --> 11:53.843
<i>ACE:</i>
<i>How much are we playing for?</i>

11:53.843 --> 11:55.054
CHRIS:
The fuck are you doing?

11:55.054 --> 11:58.143
What, are you still high?
<i>NADIA: Yeah.</i>

11:58.143 --> 12:00.230
‐ Just reflecting.

12:00.230 --> 12:02.485
[car door slams]

12:02.485 --> 12:04.573
CHRIS: Those two shit‐buckets
are waiting for you.

12:04.573 --> 12:06.661
They're out there talking
about shooting up Somalis

12:06.661 --> 12:08.288
thanks to you.

12:08.288 --> 12:10.961
Something really bad
almost happened.

12:10.961 --> 12:12.589
To Abdi, to Pop.

12:12.589 --> 12:14.467
Shit even you wouldn't be able
to live with.

12:14.467 --> 12:17.181
‐ I don't know.

12:17.181 --> 12:18.851
I find I can live with a lot.

12:22.400 --> 12:25.657
CHRIS: Turn that shit off.
It's fucking creepy.

12:25.657 --> 12:28.495
<i>[indistinct chatter over TV]</i>

12:31.167 --> 12:32.211
<i>NADIA: Come on!</i>

12:32.211 --> 12:33.631
<i>Stop that.</i>

12:33.631 --> 12:35.217
<i>Stop that, come on.</i>

12:35.217 --> 12:37.179
[tape clicks]

12:37.179 --> 12:40.185
<i>[ominous music]</i>

12:40.185 --> 12:41.898
<i>♪ ♪</i>
[Nadia and Abdi speaking Somali]

12:56.027 --> 12:57.053
[phone beeps]

13:03.733 --> 13:06.739
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

13:06.739 --> 13:09.828
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:09.828 --> 13:12.083
<i>PERSON: [over P. A. system]</i>
<i>Wheelchair, lobby for assist.</i>

13:12.083 --> 13:14.170
<i>Wheelchair to lobby</i>
<i>for assist.</i>

13:16.049 --> 13:18.638
[door clicks open]

13:18.638 --> 13:20.140
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:20.140 --> 13:21.226
[door clicks shut]

13:25.359 --> 13:28.073
POP: Inanta, I, uh...

13:29.450 --> 13:33.291
I got some bad instincts
when it comes to your brother.

13:33.291 --> 13:35.045
I know that.

13:35.045 --> 13:37.759
I made a big mistake.

13:39.387 --> 13:41.182
And I want to get square
with you,

13:41.182 --> 13:42.936
and I'll do whatever‐‐

13:42.936 --> 13:45.315
‐ Your blood results came back.

13:45.315 --> 13:49.448
The chemo hasn't given us
the outcome we had hoped for.

13:52.998 --> 13:55.962
<i>[somber music]</i>

13:55.962 --> 13:58.133
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:58.133 --> 13:59.553
‐ Okay.

14:01.974 --> 14:03.811
So what you're saying is,
we're done.

14:03.811 --> 14:05.690
NADIA: That's not
what I'm saying.

14:05.690 --> 14:08.111
There are dozens
of new therapies.

14:08.111 --> 14:09.865
Bone marrow transplants...
‐ Nah, Nadia.

14:09.865 --> 14:12.537
‐ Immunotherapy,
clinical trials.

14:14.332 --> 14:16.419
‐ Yeah, well,
maybe I don't want to fight it.

14:16.419 --> 14:18.465
NADIA: You see,
that's not how this works.

14:18.465 --> 14:20.803
I came back to fix you.

14:20.803 --> 14:22.139
‐ You tried.

14:22.139 --> 14:23.809
NADIA:
And now you're gonna try.

14:23.809 --> 14:25.479
You owe me that.

14:29.613 --> 14:33.788
[door clicks open, slams]

14:33.788 --> 14:36.042
Your PD‐1 inhibitor trial
sounds promising.

14:36.042 --> 14:37.963
I was hoping
he might be a candidate.

14:37.963 --> 14:39.340
<i>DOCTOR: He's not showing up</i>
<i>in the system.</i>

14:39.340 --> 14:41.260
Is it M‐E‐R‐R‐I‐L‐L?

14:41.260 --> 14:43.891
‐ I don't think he's used the
Veterans Health system before.

14:43.891 --> 14:46.730
<i>DOCTOR: Ever?</i>
<i>How long's he been out?</i>

14:46.730 --> 14:48.108
‐ A while.

14:48.108 --> 14:50.613
Sergeant Major Merrill
served in Iraq and, uh,

14:50.613 --> 14:52.575
well, he doesn't like
to talk about it, you know?

14:52.575 --> 14:55.205
<i>DOCTOR:</i>
<i>Hmm, he serve anywhere else?</i>

14:55.205 --> 14:56.875
<i>NADIA:</i>
<i>Afghanistan, I think.</i>

14:56.875 --> 15:00.925
<i>But he's not exactly</i>
<i>the most patriotic veteran.</i>

15:00.925 --> 15:02.721
No offense.
I know how you guys can get.

15:02.721 --> 15:04.306
<i>DOCTOR:</i>
<i>[laughs] None taken.</i>

15:04.306 --> 15:06.687
<i>What makes you think</i>
<i>he wants to join the study?</i>

15:06.687 --> 15:10.570
‐ Look, if you can get him in,
then I can convince him.

15:10.570 --> 15:12.448
Thank you, Doctor.
[button clicks]

15:21.007 --> 15:22.552
[brakes squeal]

15:22.552 --> 15:24.055
[engine stops]

15:25.015 --> 15:26.685
ACE:
[speaking French]

15:26.685 --> 15:28.188
‐ [gasps softly]

15:28.188 --> 15:31.194
<i>[ominous music]</i>

15:31.194 --> 15:37.832
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:40.880 --> 15:43.384
Abdi Howlwadaag.

15:43.384 --> 15:46.390
[speaking French]

15:46.390 --> 15:52.821
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:00.920 --> 16:03.926
[dog barking]

16:03.926 --> 16:10.940
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:11.817 --> 16:14.948
[dog huffing, barking]

16:14.948 --> 16:21.962
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:24.091 --> 16:27.097
[windshield wipers thumping]

16:37.952 --> 16:39.956
[brakes squeal]

16:41.417 --> 16:42.419
[engine stops]

16:42.419 --> 16:49.391
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:10.810 --> 17:13.816
<i>CHRIS: How are you holding up?</i>
<i>NADIA: Not great.</i>

17:13.816 --> 17:15.861
CHRIS: Come get worse.

17:15.861 --> 17:17.615
NADIA: Mm.

17:19.326 --> 17:20.746
‐ I actually thought about

17:20.746 --> 17:22.332
stopping by the church
this morning.

17:22.332 --> 17:24.211
NADIA: Pop doesn't need
thoughts and prayers.

17:24.211 --> 17:27.050
I need you
to work on him for me.

17:27.050 --> 17:28.386
Get him back in the fight.

17:30.808 --> 17:33.647
‐ I just can't imagine...

17:33.647 --> 17:35.442
I mean, he could really
just be not here.

17:35.442 --> 17:37.905
Not‐‐not at the store,
not anywhere.

17:39.283 --> 17:41.663
‐ And it will be my fault.

17:41.663 --> 17:44.753
‐ Come on, Nadia.

17:44.753 --> 17:47.550
‐ Just like Mom.

17:47.550 --> 17:49.721
‐ Your mom?

17:49.721 --> 17:51.057
NADIA: It's true.

17:51.057 --> 17:53.102
‐ You were just a kid.

17:53.102 --> 17:56.860
‐ I, um, walked out
like I was in a dream.

17:57.862 --> 17:59.783
<i>Walked right into a war.</i>

17:59.783 --> 18:03.039
I couldn't save her.

18:03.039 --> 18:06.588
<i>[dark music]</i>

18:06.588 --> 18:08.842
But this, this I can do...

18:08.842 --> 18:11.305
if he'd just fucking let me.

18:11.305 --> 18:13.434
‐ I'll work on him.

18:13.434 --> 18:16.315
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:16.315 --> 18:18.821
<i>DREW: So what can I do</i>
<i>for you, Mr. Merrill?</i>

18:18.821 --> 18:23.079
<i>POP: Say a man has something</i>
<i>on his books...</i>

18:23.079 --> 18:25.458
something bad...

18:25.458 --> 18:29.466
and he can't shift it;
he can't pay it off.

18:29.466 --> 18:32.849
It's written in blood...

18:32.849 --> 18:35.019
just soaked
right through the page.

18:36.272 --> 18:37.692
It's eating
at his fucking liver

18:37.692 --> 18:39.361
faster than the cancer.

18:40.656 --> 18:43.453
And the only way
to make it stop...

18:43.453 --> 18:47.335
is to tell the person
he did it to...

18:47.335 --> 18:48.839
'cause she don't even know.

18:50.091 --> 18:51.678
So...

18:52.805 --> 18:54.976
Should he do it?

18:54.976 --> 18:57.397
Should he tell her?

18:57.397 --> 18:59.359
‐ I guess I'd have to ask...

19:01.363 --> 19:04.161
Why is he confessing to her

19:04.161 --> 19:05.664
and not God?

